    • Class javelin.model.world.place.town.ResearchData extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • hand

          Research[] hand
          Represents a few Research options that the player or #automanager can use to advance a town. Grow should always be the first option. A value of null means that the hand is initially empty, that it's card has been spent or that there are no more valid cards of that type. These are the card types by index for non-hostile (human) Towns: 0 - Grow 1 - Native (from #realm) Upgrade. 2 - Foreign Upgrade 3 - Native Item. 4 - Foreign Item 5 - Native Monster lair, see #lairs 6 - Special card 7 - Accommodations upgrade. 8 - Transport upgrade. These are the card types by index for hostile (monster) Towns: 0 - Grow 1 - Native Monster lair, see #lairs 2-7 - RecruitOption for it to recruit an unit into WorldPlace.garrison
          See Also:
